First, let's find the intersection (A ∩ B) and the symmetric difference (A ∆ B) of sets A and B.

A ∩ B = {x | x ∈ A and x ∈ B} = {2, 4}
A ∆ B = (A - B) ∪ (B - A) = {1, 3, 5} ∪ {6, 8, 10} = {1, 3, 5, 6, 8, 10}

Now, let's find the symmetric difference of (A ∩ B) and (A ∆ B).

(A ∩ B) ∆ (A ∆ B) = ({2, 4} - {1, 3, 5, 6, 8, 10}) ∪ ({1, 3, 5, 6, 8, 10} - {2, 4})
= {1, 3, 5, 6, 8, 10} ∪ {1, 3, 5, 6, 8, 10}
= {1, 3, 5, 6, 8, 10}

So, the symmetric difference of (A ∩ B) and (A ∆ B) is {1, 3, 5, 6, 8, 10}.
